article.description:
Chasity Melvin scored a career-high 30 points
and Jennifer Rizzotti doubled her previous best with 14 assists to
lead the Cleveland Rockers to an 80-69 victory over the New York
Liberty on Friday night.
article.headline: Rockers' Melvin scores career-high 30 points
article.linkText: Melvin, Rizzotti have career nights in win vs. Liberty
article.story:
CLEVELAND (AP) -- Chasity Melvin scored a career-high 30 points
and Jennifer Rizzotti doubled her previous best with 14 assists to
lead the Cleveland Rockers to an 80-69 victory over the New York
Liberty on Friday night.

	   Melvin scored eight consecutive points for the Rockers early in
the second half to help them hold off a brief New York rally.

	   Vickie Johnson scored 19 points for the Liberty (7-5), who
opened the second half with a 10-4 run before Melvin put Cleveland
back in command.

	   The Rockers (3-5) finally displayed some of the homecourt
intensity they enjoyed last season, but had struggled to achieve
this year. Cleveland has twice lost games after leading by 14
points and is just 2-3 at home this season after going 14-2 at Gund
Arena a year ago.

	   Melvin scored 14 points to help Cleveland take a 45-34 halftime
lead. The 6-foot-3 center turned several passes from point guard
Rizzotti into easy layups.

	   Tamika Whitmore scored six points for New York in the 10-4 run
that got the Liberty within 49-44.

	   Melvin, who finished 12-for-16 from the field, then made two
free throws, a 6-foot hook shot, a layup and a putback.

	   Meanwhile, the Rockers held New York scoreless for 4:05, until
Whitmore hit a free throw with 7:54 to play that made it 58-47.

	   Crystal Robinson, who finished with 17 points, hit three
3-pointers early for New York. The Liberty hit four of five
3-pointers early, but the Rockers adjusted their defense and kept
the Liberty from attempting another long-range shot over the final
7:45 of the first half.

	   Penny Taylor added 15 points for Cleveland, which will play five
of its next seven games at home. The Liberty continue a stretch
where they play nine of their first 13 games on the road. New York
is 4-4 away from home this year.
